			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I've compiled a <a href="http://pineight.com/mw/index.php?title=Dot_clock_rates" class="postlink">list of other platforms' dot clock rates</a>. Both the SMS VDP and the NES PPU use the TMS9918 dot clock rate, which is 3/2 of the NTSC colorburst rate. This means the width of active picture is the same for both platforms, but the side-to-side positioning may differ slightly for a couple trivial reasons.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
